we can use query selector to grab elements

queryselector will select only the first mathcing elemment

document.getElementById - returns the first matching element

if not found returns null


we can use style property to style the elements-

document.getElementById('div1').style.backgroundColor ="red"

document.getElementById('div1').style.padding = '10px'

______________________________________________________________


document.querySelector('#id') - will get the element with matching id

document.querySelector('.className') - will get the element with matching className

document.querySelector('h1') - will get the element with matching tag




